    "cityHangzhou": "Hangzhou",
    "descHangzhou": "China's poetic paradise on West Lake, famous for tea and silk.",
    "longDescHangzhou": "<p>Hangzhou, the capital of Zhejiang province, is widely considered one of China's most beautiful cities. Its legendary <strong>West Lake</strong> (\u897f\u6e56) has inspired poets, painters, and scholars for over a thousand years. The city seamlessly blends natural beauty, historical grandeur, and a thriving modern economy as the home of Alibaba.</p><p>West Lake's serene waters, surrounded by hills, pagodas, and gardens, offer boat rides, cycling paths, and scenic walks year-round. The area around the lake is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of China's most visited tourist destinations.</p><h3 id=\"west-lake\" class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">West Lake</h3><p><strong>West Lake</strong> (\u897f\u6e56) is Hangzhou's crown jewel. A freshwater lake surrounded by gardens, temples, and man-made islands, it has been a source of artistic inspiration for centuries. <strong>Boat rides</strong> (especially the enclosed \"Chinese style\" rowboats), walking the <strong>Su Causeway</strong>, and visiting <strong>Leifeng Pagoda</strong> for sunset views are quintessential Hangzhou experiences.</p><p><strong>Opening:</strong> 24/7. <strong>Best time:</strong> Early morning for misty lake views; evening for Leifeng Pagoda sunset.</p><h3 id=\"longjing-tea\" class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">Longjing Tea Plantations</h3><p>Hangzhou is the birthplace of <strong>Longjing (Dragon Well) tea</strong>, one of China's most famous green teas. The tea plantations around <strong>Meijiawu</strong> (\u6885\u5bb6\u575e) offer tours, tea-picking experiences, and tastings in traditional tea houses set among rolling green hills.</p><h3 id=\"grand-canal\" class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">The Grand Canal</h3><p>Hangzhou marks the southern terminus of the <strong>Grand Canal</strong> (\u4eac\u676d\u5927\u8fd0\u6cb3), the world's longest artificial river. The historic canal area has been beautifully restored, with pedestrianized streets, cafes, and boat tours.</p><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">How to get there</h3><p><strong>By air:</strong> Hangzhou Xiaoshan International Airport (HGH) has domestic and regional international flights. Airport metro Line 1 connects to the city center (~45 min).</p><p><strong>By train:</strong> Hangzhou East Railway Station is a major high-speed rail hub. Shanghai (~45 min), Beijing (~4.5h), Xi'an (~5h) by high-speed train.</p><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">Best time to visit</h3><p>Spring (Mar-May) and autumn (Sep-Nov) are ideal. Summer can be hot and crowded; winter is quiet but occasionally foggy.</p><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">Getting around</h3><ul><li><strong>Metro:</strong> Extensive network. Hangzhou Metro app or transit card.</li><li><strong>Bicycle:</strong> Cycling around West Lake is highly recommended.</li><li><strong>Didi / Taxi:</strong> Readily available throughout the city.</li></ul><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">Suggested itineraries</h3><p><strong>1 day:</strong> West Lake morning (Su Causeway walk, boat ride) -- Lunch at lakeside restaurant -- Tea plantation afternoon -- Grand Canal evening.</p><p><strong>3 days:</strong> Day 1: West Lake + Leifeng Pagoda; Day 2: Longjing tea villages + Meijiawu; Day 3: Hefang Street + Grand Canal + silk shopping.</p><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-2\">Practical tips</h3><ul><li><strong>Tea:</strong> Buy directly from tea farms for better prices and authenticity.</li><li><strong>Weekends:</strong> West Lake is extremely crowded on weekends -- visit on weekdays.</li><li><strong>Silk:</strong> Hangzhou is China's silk capital. The China National Silk Museum offers tours and shopping.</li></ul>",
    "ogTitleHangzhou": "Hangzhou Travel Guide - West Lake, Tea Culture & Ancient Heritage",
    "ogDescHangzhou": "Explore Hangzhou with guides to West Lake, Longjing tea plantations, and the ancient Grand Canal. Plan your Hangzhou trip with insider tips.",
