    "longDescJiuzhaigou": "<p>Jiuzhaigou is renowned for its vivid turquoise lakes, multi-tiered waterfalls and pristine alpine valleys \u2013 a scenic gem in Sichuan province.</p><h3>Highlights</h3><ul><li><strong>Rize Valley</strong> \u2013 colorful lakes and clear water reflections.</li><li><strong>Shuzheng Valley</strong> \u2013 classic views of layered waterfalls.</li><li><strong>Hiking & Photography</strong> \u2013 boardwalk trails provide easy access to viewpoints.</li></ul>",
    "longDescYangtze": "<p>The Yangtze is China's longest river, famous for the dramatic Three Gorges and popular river cruises that combine scenery with cultural visits.</p><h3>Highlights</h3><ul><li><strong>Three Gorges</strong> \u2013 steep-sided gorges carved by the river offering spectacular views.</li><li><strong>Yangtze Cruises</strong> \u2013 multi-day cruise options between Chongqing and Yichang.</li><li><strong>Cultural stops</strong> \u2013 riverside towns, temples and local markets.</li></ul>",
    "longDescIching": "<p>The <strong>I Ching</strong> (also written <em>iching</em>, Chinese: <strong>\u6613\u7ecf</strong>) \u2013 literally the <em>Book of Changes</em> \u2013 is one of the oldest Chinese classics. It combines cosmology, philosophy and a system of 64 hexagrams used historically for divination and decision-making.</p><h3>History & structure</h3><p>The iching developed over millennia. Each of its 64 hexagrams is formed from six lines (broken or unbroken). Traditional commentaries \u2013 the Ten Wings \u2013 expanded the text into a rich philosophical work used by scholars and sages.</p><h3>How iching divination works</h3><p>Modern iching methods use coins or yarrow stalk techniques to generate a hexagram. Interpreting the iching hexagram involves reading its meaning, line transformations, and how it relates to your question.</p><h3>Why read the I Ching today?</h3><ul><li><strong>Philosophical insight:</strong> iching offers frameworks for change and decision-making.</li><li><strong>Cultural context:</strong> Understanding \u6613\u7ecf deepens appreciation for Chinese thought, history and literature.</li><li><strong>Practical uses:</strong> meditation, creative prompts, and reflective decision processes.</li></ul><h3>Further reading & resources</h3><p>Recommended translations and commentaries include works by Richard Wilhelm (translated by Cary F. Baynes), and modern commentaries that explain iching hexagrams in contemporary terms.</p><h3>Learn more</h3><p>If you are visiting China and interested in cultural tours, ask local museums or cultural centers about lectures and exhibits related to I Ching and Chinese classical philosophy.</p>",
